 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucyrz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cyrz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#333333>(10/1/02 3:55:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1022.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: horse ...</span><hr size=1> I have a 9k horse, and it's slower then jboots or run3. Not by much, but it is slower.<br>
<br>
The mana regen w/o sitting aggro is very nice. Just hotkey and pratic typing /dism(ount)<br>
<br>
Why? My mage died more times the day he got the horse then he had in the previous 5 or 6 levels of soloing. The horse takes a few seconds to get up to speed, stuns reset that, etc. With jboots or even normal runspeed, I can move away from a mob quickly, letting pet get the aggro. With a horse, I took a lot more damage trying to get away, and even once died to a rooted mob because I couldn't move away fast enough on the horse. After I got proficent at /dism (can't use hotkeys while casting) and hotkeyed it, the horse became a usefull tool instead of a death trap.<br>
<br>
Another reason to pratice typing /dism is because you can't duck on a horse. Cast the wrong spell, cast a nuke on a target that dies before the nuke finishes casting, or even realize 3 seconds into the nuke you have the wrong target, and you have to either move enough that you can't channel the spell (and still wait for the full cast time of the spell to run out) or type /dism, duck, and come right back up to nuke, heal pet, chain summon, switch targets so you DS the tank instead of the mob, whatever you did wrong. Remember, that dismount hotkey doesn't work while casting.<br>
<br>
All in all, the 9k horse, to me, is worth it, but mostly because of the coolness factor, and to a lesser extant, the medding without standing. For Travel, Jboots are cheaper, safer, and faster. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#333333>- </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower>The Magician's Tower</a><font color=#333333> - </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28>Equipment</a> <font color=#333333> - </font><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/">The Mage Compendium</a><font color=#333333> - </font>  <br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">Upgrade your account to ezSupporter...</a></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">...and never see another ad or pop-up again</a></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START BOTTOM AD SCRIPT -->
